				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/barredowl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6001754); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6001754&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183411" alt="barredowl" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6001754)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/barredowl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6001754); return false;" >barredowl</a></span> <span class="odate time_1603076049 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Oct 2020 02:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4799216">
									

<p>The chat logs, especially the codename gag with Bright, made me chuckle, but I can't help but feel the last log plays the concept too straight. Establishing that the SCP wiki is the product of the real SCP Foundation is a neat concept, but this article doesn't really take that to its full potential, instead making some surface-level jokes about what that would mean, and sorta just&#8230; dropping it early. The second half of the log exemplifies this &#8212; the punchline about masquerading as a creative writing site is kinda expected given everything else in the article, and fizzles out pretty quickly. It doesn't give that good of a final impression for me and sorta feels limp as an ending.</p>
<p>Still upvoting, because I enjoyed a majority of the jokes here, but I think this can be revised a bit further so that this article sticks the landing.</p>

							</div>

								
					
